[5] New Zealand
Date: Sat 9 Jul 2022 21:09 NZST
https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/300633595/new-zealands-first-case-of-monkeypox-detected-in-auckland


New Zealand's 1st case of monkeypox has been detected in Auckland, the Ministry of Health has announced.

The person in their 30s is in isolation at home and has recently returned from overseas travel in a country with reported cases of monkeypox. A "very small" number of contacts are being advised to watch for symptoms, and there is no evidence of community transmission.

Monkeypox is a viral zoonotic disease, meaning it is able to pass from animals to humans.

