[This report underscores the dilemma of having to make decisions in the face of an ongoing outbreak when relevant data are unavailable. There is not time available to carry out the relevant experiments when transmission is occurring currently. Clearly, one dose of the vaccine is better than none. Duration of immunity will become clearer as recipients of a single dose are naturally challenged over time. - Mod.TY]

